Its seat is located in the town of Kungsör. The present municipality was formed in 1971 when Kungsör and Kung Karl (from which Kungsör had been detached as a market town (köping) in 1907) were amalgamated Kungsör is located at the western end of lake Mälaren. The landscape is open, dominated by fields and meadows. == Localities == * Kungsör (seat) * Valskog Historically, the town grew around the Royal Mansion that King Gustav Vasa had built in the 16th century. Parts of the mansion are still preserved and open for visits.
